 detailed review of prior work in this area, a rich exploration of new empirical data and a highly innovative and robust approach to the study of ‘music worlds’.Written in an accessible style, this book is essential reading for anybody with an interest in either UK punk and post-punk or the impact of social networks on cultural life and the potential of social network analysis to explore this impact.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPunk culturexGreat BritainxGreat Britain. 0aPunk culturezGreat Britain. 0aPunk rock musicxHistory and criticismxGreat Britain. 0aPunk rock musiczGreat BritainxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aHoward Becker.  aLiverpool.  aLondon.  aManchester.  aSamuel Gilmore.  aSheffield.  amass media networks.  amusic worlds.  apost-punk world.  apunk.  asocial networks.  asociological reality.  asubculture.1 aCrossley, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779993740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847799937423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847799937/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles